# Alembic Migration Rules

## Always set `down_revision` to the current head

Before creating a new migration, find the current head:

```bash
python -m alembic heads
```

Set `down_revision` to that value — **never hardcode an older revision**.

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — points to the current head
revision: str = "20260227_002"
down_revision: Union[str, None] = "20260226_002"  # result of `alembic heads`

# ❌ WRONG — skips an intermediate migration, creates two heads
down_revision: Union[str, None] = "20260226_001"
```

## Verify after writing

```bash
python -m alembic heads  # must show exactly ONE head
```

If you see two heads, one of your migrations has the wrong `down_revision`. Update it to point to the other head so the chain becomes linear.
